%S A397875 2,3,0,4,1,4,6,4,5,6,9,1,0,3,3,9,0,9,5,4,9,3,7,3,3,9,0,3,6,4,6,6,9,3,
%T A397875 0,7,3,9,0,8,9,7,8,2,0,0,4,1,3,0,5,0,3,7,9,1,4,4,4,3,6,3,8,9,8,1,4,4,
%U A397875 8,7,2,1,1,6,3,5,1,3,5,1,3,1,3,7,8,3,3,2,6,3
%N A397875 Decimal expansion of the dihedral angle, in radians, between any two adjacent faces in a canonical (dual-uniform) heptagonal trapezohedron.
%C A397875 The heptagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the heptagonal antiprism.
%H A397875 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397875/b397875.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397875 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalTrapezohedron.html">Heptagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397875 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antitegum">Heptagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397875 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%F A397875 Equals arccos(1 + 1/(cos(Pi/7) - 3/2)) = arccos(1 + 1/(A073052 - 3/2)).
%F A397875 Equals arccos(c), where c = -0.66936... is the smallest root of 13*x^3 - x^2 - 5*x + 1.
%e A397875 2.304146456910339095493733903646693073908978200413...
%t A397875 First[RealDigits[ArcCos[1 + 1/(Cos[Pi/7] - 3/2)], 10, 100]]
%t A397875 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397875 First[RealDigits[First[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 7}, "DihedralAngles"]], 10, 100]]
%Y A397875 Cf. A397867 (volume), A397868 (surface area), A397869 (inradius), A397870 (midradius), A397871 (height).
%Y A397875 Cf. A397872 (long edge).
%Y A397875 Cf. A397873 (small face angle), A397874 (large face angle).
%Y A397875 Cf. A394076 and A394077 (dihedral angles of the dual).
%Y A397875 Cf. A073052.
%K A397875 nonn,cons,easy,new
%O A397875 1,1
